quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  40,66,"Say: “I have been forbidden that I may pay obedience to those whom you invoke besides Allah when Al-Bayyinat has reached me from my Nourisher-Sustainer. And I have been ordered that I may submit in Islam to the Nourisher-Sustainer of the worlds"
  40,67,"He it is Who created you (as Adam) from clay, afterwards from Nutfah, then from a clinging mass. Then He brings forth you as a child, then keeps you growing in order that you may reach to your full strength; then He keeps you alive that you may become senior citizens. And of you is that whose life-span is completed before (reaching this senior age), and (all these differences in age exist to make you realise) that you reach an appointed (and) specified term (or life-span), and perchance you may use intellect"
  40,68,"He it is Who gives life and causes death. And when He decided a matter, then surely what (is a fact is that) He will say to it: \"Be!” So it becomes (a thing that exists)"
  40,69,Have you not seen towards those who dispute against Ayaatillahe how are they being turned away (from the Message)
  40,70,"Those who have belied Al-Kitab and that with what We sent therewith Our Messengers, soon they will come to know (their fate). [Certain ordainments in Al-Kitab, like Itikaf, Salat, Tawaf, Umra, Hajj and Zakat adopt a practical format when being implemented. The format adhered to by all the Prophets of Allah is the only format recognised by Him. It is preserved by Him at and around Kaba. See Verse No 2/125, 17/77-79 and]"
  40,71,"When (there are) iron-collars in their necks, and (they stand hand-cuffed and fettered in) chains, they shall be dragged (along) —"
  40,72,"in the boiling water, then in the Fire they will be thrown"
  40,73,"then it is said to them: “Where are those whom you used to join as partners —"
  40,74,"besides Allah?” They said: “They have vanished from us. Nay, we did not use to invoke any thing in previous (world).” Thus Allah allows the disbelievers to lose the track"
  40,75,"This is to you because of what you used to enjoy in the earth without right, and because you used to rejoice insolently"
  40,76,Enter the gates of Hell becoming abiders therein. So (what an) evil abode for the arrogants
  40,77,"So be patient, the promise of Allah is true. So if whatever We may show you — some of what We promise them, or We cause you to die, then to Us they shall be returned back"
  40,78,"And indeed, We have sent Messengers before you; out of them is that whom We have narrated unto you, and of them is that whom We did not narrate unto you. And it was not (suitable) for a Messenger that he may approach with a credential — except under permission of Allah. So when the decree of Allah proceeded, the decision was taken in full justice, and then and there lost those who indulged in falsehood and forgery"
  40,79,"Allah is He Who has made quadrupeds for you (so) that you may ride on some of them, and some of them you eat"
  40,80,"And for you therein are benefits, and that you may reach by their means (the) desire which is in your chests; and on them and on the ships you are taken as a rider"
  40,81,And He makes you see His Signs. Then which of the Signs of Allah you shall deny
  40,82,"Did they then not travel through the earth so (that) they may see what was the final end of those (who passed) before them? They were more numerous than them, and mightier in strength; and the landmarks and monuments (they left) on the earth. So did not benefit them whatever they used to earn (through their beliefs and deeds)"
  40,83,So when came to them their Messengers with Al-Bayyinat they remained fully satisfied with what was with them out of knowledge. And surrounded them (as punishment) whatever they used to ridicule thereat
  40,84,"So when they watched Our Punishment (about to seize them) they said: “We have Believed in Allah — His Oneness, and we have rejected with what we remained thereby as polytheists"
  40,85,Then (at such a stage) does not become their faith that it will give them (any) benefit when they have already sensed Our torment. This is the Sunnah of Allah which has definitely functioned amongst His Ibad. And then and there the disbelievers lost utterly
  41,1,M
  41,2,"(It is a) Descent from Ar-Rahman, Ar-Rahim"
  41,3,Kitab (‘Book’) — its Verses have been fully detailed — Quran (‘Reading’) in Arabic — (meant) for a nation who know (and appreciate the importance and utility of the Divine Book)
  41,4,"Bashir (‘the transmitter of glad tidings’. This is used as an attribute for the Divine Scripture), and Nazeer (‘Warner’. This also is an attribute for Allah’s Book); but most of them have remained unconcerned (of this Book), so they do not listen"
  41,5,"And they said: “Our hearts are under coverings against that to which you invite us; and in our ears is a blockage; and between us and between you is a barrier. So carry on your deeds, surely we are those who act (according to our inclinations and knowledge).”"
  41,6,"Say: “Certainly, what (is a fact is that) I am a human like you. It is inspired in me that what (is true is that) your Ilah (God) is One Ilah. So be steadfast to Him and invoke Him for forgiveness. And woe to Al-Mushrikun —"
  41,7,"those who do not pay Zakat, and they, regarding the Hereafter — they (are) disbelievers"
  41,8,"Truly, those who have Believed and have performed righteous deeds — for them is a reward not prohibited"